name: bcaa211
blurb: Branched Chain Amino Acids (BCAAs) refers to three amino acids: leucine, isoleucine, and valine. For people with low dietary protein intake, BCAA supplementation can promote muscle protein synthesis and increase muscle growth over time. Supplementation can also be used to prevent fatigue in novice athletes.

name: betaalanine
blurb: Beta-alanine is a modified version of the amino acid alanine. Beta-alanine has been shown to enhance muscular endurance. Beta-alanine supplementation can also improve moderate- to high-intensity cardiovascular exercise performance, like rowing or sprinting. When beta-alanine is ingested, it turns into the molecule carnosine, which acts as an acid buffer in the body. Carnosine is stored in cells and released in response to drops in pH. Large doses of beta-alanine may cause a tingling feeling called paresthesia. It is a harmless side effect.

name: caffeine
blurb: Caffeine is a powerful stimulant, and it can be used to improve physical strength and endurance. It is classified as a nootropic because it sensitizes neurons and provides mental stimulation. Caffeineâ€™s main mechanism concerns antagonizing adenosine receptors. Adenosine causes sedation and relaxation when it acts upon its receptors, located in the brain. Caffeine prevents this action and causes alertness and wakefulness. This inhibition of adenosine can influence the dopamine, serotonin, acetylcholine, and adrenaline systems.

name: creatine_cee
blurb: Creatine is a molecule that's produced in the body from amino acids. It's primarily made in the liver and to a lesser extent in the kidneys and pancreas. It stores high-energy phosphate groups in the form of phosphocreatine which are donated to ADP, regenerating it to ATP, the primary energy carrier in the body. This role in energy production is particularly relevant under conditions of high energy demand such as intense physical or mental activity. Creatine can be found in some foods and is most prevalent in meat and fish. Athletes commonly take it as a powder or in capsules.

name: larganine
blurb: L-Arginine is a conditionally essential amino acid found in the diet. It is a dietary supplement used mostly by athletic people because it is the amino acid that directly produces nitric oxide via the nitric oxide synthase enzymes.

name: lcitrulline
blurb: L-Citrulline is one of the three dietary amino acids in the urea cycle, alongside L-arginine and L-Ornithine. Taking L-citrulline increases plasma levels of ornithine and arginine and improves the ammonia recycling process and nitric oxide metabolism. Consequently, it is used in areas where nitric oxide is relevant, namely athletic performance, and vascular health, and erectile dysfunction. There are very few foods that have notable amounts of citrulline, watermelon being a notable exception.

name: lisoleucine
blurb: L-Isoleucine is a branched chain amino acid (BCAA) that helps the body to produce energy and aids in athletic endurance. It also helps promote muscle growth when taken in conjunction with exercise. L Isoleucine can be found in different foods, but taking a supplement is often the best way to ensure you're getting enough.

name: lleucine
blurb: L-Leucine is a branched chain amino acid (BCAA) that helps increase athletic performance. BCAA's help promote lean muscle growth and aid in muscle recovery. L-Leucine is particularly beneficial in boosting athletic endurance. It is also the most anabolic of all the amino acids, meaning it promotes the building of muscle tissue.

name: ltheanine
blurb: L-Theanine is an amino acid that is not common in the diet and not one of the essential amino acids or even one of the common nonessential amino acids. It is found in meaningful amounts in tea, but otherwise supplementation is the main source of it. L-Theanine has structural similarity to glutamine and both neurotransmitters that are produced from it (GABA and glutamate). It is known to reach the brain and influence its function following oral ingestion.

name: lvaine
blurb: Valine is one of the three branched-chain amino acids (BCAAs) and is essential for human nutrition. It has been shown to aid in exercise recovery, boost athletic endurance, and assist in muscle maintenance. Additionally, valine supports liver function and promotes gallbladder health. Our L-Valine is a pure and potent form of the amino acid that can be taken as part of a daily supplement regimen or used before, during, or after physical activity.

name: niacin
blurb: Vitamin B3 refers to the molecule commonly called nicotinic acid, or niacin, though it may also refer to the other vitamin B3 vitamer, called nicotinamide. Vitamin B3 is necessary to support the function of many enzymes.

name: taurine
blurb: Taurine (L-taurine) is a sulfur-containing amino acid not involved in protein synthesis but omnipresent in your body. It is essential to cardiovascular function and the development and function of the brain, retina, and skeletal muscle.
